<TITLE> Asia XI win despite Pollock batting heroics </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BANGALORE, India, June 6 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Shaun Pollock struck his maiden one-day international century on Wednesday but failed to prevent Asia XI from scoring a 34-run win over Africa XI in the first of three matches. Pollock, 33, one-day cricket's top-ranked all-rounder, lifted the innings from 87 for seven in reply to Asia XI's 317 for nine before the African combined side were all out for 283 in 47.5 overs. Batting at number seven, he dominated a 107-run ninth wicket partnership with Kenyan Thomas Odoyo (39) and put on 67 for the eighth with Zimbabwe's Elton Chigumbara (40) before being the last man out. He struck 19 fours and a six facing just 110 balls after playing as a batsmen only following a recent foot surgery. Pakistan batsman Mohammad Yousuf top-scored with 66 and skipper Mahela Jayawardene struck 65 and Mohammad Asif and Zaheer Khan shared five wickets to reduce the innings to 31 for five in reply before Pollock's heroics. The second and final games will be played in Chennai at the weekend
